<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 07 at 3:31PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Granville, Wake, east central Chatham, southeastern Durham and
southwestern Franklin Counties through 415 PM EDT...
At 331 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Cary, moving northeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Raleigh, Cary, Wake Forest, Garner, Fuquay-Varina, Franklinton, Bunn,
RDU International, Apex and Holly Springs.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 900 PM EDT for central North
Carolina.</instruction>
